-- Pound Strengthens to Below 82 Pence Per Euro First Time Since November '08
-- Matthew Brown
-- 2010-06-24T08:31:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/pound-strengthens-to-below-82-pence-per-euro-first-time-since-november-08.html

          
          
             The pound strengthened to below 82
pence per euro for the first time since November 2008.  
 The British currency appreciated to 81.98 pence per euro
before trading at 82.07 pence as of 9:31 a.m. in London.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Brown in London at 
 mbrown42@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
